------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vendored third-party data
------------------------------------------------------------------------

The character-conformance engine builds on third-party data tables. As each is
vendored it is recorded here with its upstream source and license:

1. JIS X 0213:2004 mapping table (Project X0213, https://x0213.org/codetable/).
   "You can use, modify, distribute this table freely." Used to derive the
   JIS 第1/2/3/4 水準 classifier.

2. 青空文庫 外字注記辞書 (CC0 1.0) — gaiji description ⇔ codepoint, the basis of
   the gaiji reverse index.

3. 旧字体・異体字 → 新字体 mapping (joyo-kyujitai.tsv). The underlying data is
   the 常用漢字表 (内閣告示, public domain); the machine-readable table is derived
   from new-village/joyo-kanji (Apache-2.0,
   https://github.com/new-village/joyo-kanji).
